        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>[6 Queen Anne Street]</placeName>
                    <salute>My dear D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Wrigley—</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I wrote to you about half-a year ago stating that I wished to place Horace with a private tutor after Christmas, which has just passed; &amp; received from you a very kind answer, in consequence of which &amp; from not having then heard of a Tutor, I sent Horace with your permission— back to school until, as I stated in my letter, after Easter.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I have now agreed with the Rev C. R Rouse<ref target="#foot.f3"/> to receive him, &amp; he has written to you as he tells me for Horace’s character. M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Rouse informs me that he has heard from you in reply that you have received no notice from me of Horace’s removal. I thought my letter was clear that I intended to place Horace with a Private Tutor after Easter, &amp; I am very sorry that there sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> have been this misunderstanding, I hear that Leonard<ref target="#foot.f4"/> is working capitally &amp; getting on well.—</p>
<p>Pray believe me | My dear D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Wrigley | Yours very sincerely | C. Darwin <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/> <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">Mar 7<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> | P.S from <hi rend="italic">[</hi>Rouse<hi rend="italic">]</hi></p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.1 I wrote] <hi rend="italic">after del</hi> ‘When I proposed to remove Horace to a Private Tutor last Christmas, | In | When I answered your very kind letter’ </note>
